The global extreme lateral interbody fusion (XLIF) surgery market is segmented based on product type, procedure type, and end-user. In terms of product type, the market is divided into standalone XLIF systems and integrated XLIF systems. Standalone XLIF systems are expected to witness substantial growth due to their effectiveness in treating spinal disorders. Integrated XLIF systems, on the other hand, offer enhanced precision and control during surgery. When it comes to procedure type, the market is categorized into mini-open and open XLIF surgery. Mini-open procedures are becoming increasingly popular due to their minimal invasiveness and quicker recovery times. Open XLIF surgery, although more traditional, still holds a significant market share. By end-user, the market is segmented into hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, and specialty clinics. Hospitals dominate the market due to the high volume of XLIF surgeries performed in these settings.

